    term: "AI Agents",
    slug: "ai-agents",
    definition: "AI agents are autonomous software programs that perceive their environment, make decisions, and take actions to achieve specific objectives without continuous human direction. In business, AI agents handle tasks like client communication, data processing, scheduling, and workflow coordination by combining language understanding, decision logic, and system integrations.",
    simpleExplanation: "An AI agent is like a digital team member that can handle tasks on its own within boundaries you set. Unlike a regular tool that waits for you to click a button, an agent monitors incoming work, decides what to do, and takes action. When it encounters something outside its boundaries, it escalates to a human.",
    businessExample: "A real estate brokerage deploys an AI agent for lead qualification. When a prospect submits an inquiry, the agent initiates a conversation, asks qualifying questions about budget and timeline, evaluates responses against criteria, and either schedules a showing with the appropriate agent or provides relevant listings. The agent handles 80 percent of inquiries without human involvement.",
