    definition: "Process automation is the use of technology to execute defined business processes with minimal human intervention. In the context of AI, process automation extends traditional rule-based automation by adding the ability to handle unstructured data, make contextual decisions, and adapt to variations, making previously unautomatable processes candidates for automation.",
    simpleExplanation: "Process automation means having technology run a business process from start to finish based on rules you define. Traditional process automation can only handle situations that follow exact rules. AI-enhanced process automation can handle variations, read documents that are not perfectly formatted, and make simple judgment calls, which means more of your processes can be automated than was previously possible.",
